, The American West: An Interpretive History, this volume will be an essential resource for scholars, students, and general readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFrontier and pioneer lifezWest (U.S.). 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311053801440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016059840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300160598423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300160598/original  a978-3-11-053801-4  Yale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles